[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Right alloca redzone:    cb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mmongoose[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp0z4el6rj[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA stack-buffer-overflow was detected in the `mg_json_get` function of the Mongoose [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase [0m[1;39m([0m[39msrc/mongoose/src/json.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The overflow occurs when writing to a local [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray named `nesting` beyond its allocated bounds. The issue was uncovered by [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer via the project’s fuzzing harness.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue observed:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - AddressSanitizer reports a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte write overflow on the stack at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `nesting` buffer in `mg_json_get`.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The invalid write is triggered during a call to `mg_json_get` from the fuzz [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtarget function [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in `src/mongoose/test/fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:81[0m[39m`.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The overflow location is reported at `src/mongoose/src/json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Stack-buffer-overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39moverflow of a fixed-size stack array[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important observations:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The crash reproduces reliably with the provided testcase under libFuzzer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. AddressSanitizer’s shadow bytes indicate writing into the right redzone of the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack frame.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The local variable `nesting` in `mg_json_get` spans bytes [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m62[0m[39m of the stack [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mframe; the write at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m goes past its upper bound.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. No evidence in the report suggests custom stack unwinding or exotic [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontrol-flow mechanisms that would invalidate the finding.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas for further investigation:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The implementation of `mg_json_get` in `src/mongoose/src/json.c`, especially [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe logic around the `nesting` array and index management.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. The fuzz test driver in `src/mongoose/test/fuzz.c`, line [0m[1;36m81[0m[39m, to understand how[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minputs are passed into `mg_json_get`.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Any related JSON-parsing utilities or helper functions called within [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get` that may influence the size or indexing of `nesting`.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis evaluation focuses solely on observing and cataloguing the overflow issue; no [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot-cause analysis or remediation steps are included.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Reconcile the mismatch between nesting buffer size [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth‐limit checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and tighten the guards to prevent [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moff‐by‐one writes:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `src/mongoose/src/json.c`, change the declaration of the local `nesting` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray from[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      to[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      This ensures the stack buffer can hold as many entries as the code’s depth [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks allow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Update the “too deep” conditions in both the object‐entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray‐entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m handlers to be inclusive of the limit. Replace[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      with[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      in both places [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m[1;36m167[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m176[0m[39m in `json.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This prevents `depth [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` from slipping past the guard and overwriting [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Leave the public macros in `src/mongoose/src/json.h` intact so that users [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverriding one or the other aren’t unexpectedly broken. The code now uses [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` for both buffer allocation and bounds checking; the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` macro remains defined but unused in `mg_json_get`.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. No other functionality or tests will change: all existing logic around `ed`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pos`, `ci`, `ei` and the return‐codes [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntouched. The fuzz harness and JSON‐parsing behavior are preserved exactly, except[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat pathological inputs leading to >[0m[1;36m60[0m[39m nested braces/brackets now yield [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` rather than corrupting the stack.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification and Side‐Effects:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By sizing `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` to the same limit the code enforces, we eliminate the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moff‐by‐one overflow without altering the parsing state‐machine.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tightening the guard from `>` to `>=` closes an edge‐case hole that would [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallow one out‐of‐bounds write even if the buffer were the correct size.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The only side‐effect is a slightly larger stack frame [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m60[0m[39m bytes instead of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is negligible.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests and the fuzz harness continue to operate unmodified; inputs[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat legitimately exceed the nesting limit now fail gracefully.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis approach is minimal, preserves all existing logic paths, and directly [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maddresses the AddressSanitizer report’s root cause.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A libFuzzer run on `mongoose/test/fuzz.c` invoked `mg_json_get` with inputs [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleading to a write outside the bounds of a stack array.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer output pinpoints the overflow at `json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`, writing to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` when `depth` reaches or exceeds the compile-time constant [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontrolling the array size.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack frame shows `nesting` occupies offsets [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but the write occurs at [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The local buffer `nesting` is sized by a macro [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that does [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot match the maximum nesting handled by the code.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The call stack traces back to `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `fuzz.c`, confirming [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe harness triggers the overflow.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No other memory regions are implicated; the overflow is strictly on the local [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting` array.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/json.c`, lines around the declaration of `nesting` were changed from:  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  to:  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In the blocks handling `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` characters, the checks  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  were updated to  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Rebuild and retest under the same fuzz harness. [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLog after patch  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Fuzzer invocation and libFuzzer parameters remain identical.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer again reports a write at `json.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[39m`, same offset out-of-bounds[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon the same stack array.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack frame and shadow‐byte diagnostics show the local array still too small [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor the actual nesting depth reached under fuzzing.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39msupported depth.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code path inside `mg_json_get` that increments `depth` and indexes [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, ensuring all increments are guarded by correct bounds checks.  [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39massociated headers.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m:#include [0m[32m"str.h"[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m13[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m14[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Error return values - negative. Successful returns are >= [0m[1;36m0[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m15:e[0m[39mnum [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m, MG_JSON_INVALID = [0m[1;36m-2[0m[39m, MG_JSON_NOT_FOUND = [0m[1;36m-3[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m16[0m[39m:int [0m[1;35mmg_json_get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct mg_str json, const char *path, int *toklen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root‐cause analysis:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` in `mg_json_get` was originally sized by [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but the code allowed nesting levels up to [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Patching just the declaration in `json.c` to use `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` without[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madjusting the header definitions did not actually increase the array’s size at [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompile time [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe build evidently continued to see a [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m‐byte buffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow always happens at the line `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;` in the `[0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbranch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjson.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m once `depth` exceeds the true buffer length.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy to fix:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Unify the two macros so that the compile‐time buffer size and the runtime [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguard use exactly the same limit.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Ensure that after the fix, any attempt to go beyond the allowed nesting level[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturns `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` before any write to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Preserve existing behavior [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e., enforce a maximum nesting level[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m while [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreventing out‐of‐bounds writes.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed patch plan:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `src/json.h`:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Change the macro definitions so that `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` is always set to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same value as `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - For clarity, pick one canonical name [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwe choose `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malias the other to it.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Remove the hard‐coded literal `[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m` from `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and define it [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min terms of `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This guarantees that both the buffer and the checks reference the same [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstant at compile time.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      Proposed edit in `src/json.h`:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```diff[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -#endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +[0m[35m/[0m[39m* Alias MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH to the same value for buffer sizing *[0m[35m/[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +#endif[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In `src/json.c`:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Confirm the declaration of the stack buffer now reads:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```c[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m now equals [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Keep the depth checks in both the `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` branches using `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Ensure these checks occur *before* any `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` write.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of existing logic:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing API and behavior are unchanged: any path deeper than the configured [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaximum returns `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP`.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer harness, test suite, and all existing code paths remain unmodified and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue exercising the same code; only the header and buffer sizing change to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclose the overflow.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential side effects and mitigation:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack usage for `mg_json_get` increases from ~[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes to ~[0m[1;36m60[0m[39m bytes for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `nesting` array. This is negligible for typical applications.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If downstream code or build scripts override `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to a custom[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msmaller value, `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` will adapt automatically, maintaining safety.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other utility functions or fuzzing harnesses are changed, so no regressions[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare expected in unrelated components.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Similar precedent:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It is common in parsers to unify buffer‐size macros and guard macros to the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame constant [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., HTTP header parsing limits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This ensures that runtime bounds [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks align exactly with compile‐time buffer sizes.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>src/json.h:[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m16[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue arises when running the libFuzzer-based JSON parser [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`mg_json_get`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m under AddressSanitizer. A one-byte stack-buffer-overflow is [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreported in `mg_json_get` at `json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`, where a local array named `nesting` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis overflowed by one byte.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch attempt was made that swapped and renamed the `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` macro definitions in `json.h`, and modified the depth‐check [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconditions in `json.c` from  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```  [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto  [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```  [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDespite applying this patch, the same AddressSanitizer report—overflow of the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting` array at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m—reoccurs, indicating that the attempted change did not[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent the stack overflow.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- When invoking the fuzzer with a testcase, AddressSanitizer aborts with a [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow in the function `mg_json_get` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefined in `src/json.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash stack trace pinpoints a write of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at address corresponding to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m in the local array `nesting`, whose bounds are roughly `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This indicates that the code is writing one byte past the end of `nesting`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The failure consistently reproduces in the fuzz test entrypoint [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `src/test/fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:81:3[0m[39m`.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/json.h`, the default values and macro names for maximum JSON [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting/depth were swapped:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```diff[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  -#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  -#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  +#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  +#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  …[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  -#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  -#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  +#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  +#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/json.c`, the checks guarding against excessive nesting levels were [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maltered from:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```diff[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  -if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  +if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  for both object [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and array [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m cases.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- These changes adjust the numeric threshold and comparison operator but leave the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocal storage for nesting state unchanged.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After rebuilding with the patch, running the same fuzz testcase still triggers [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe identical AddressSanitizer error at `json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash report shows the same overflow of the `nesting` array [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset [0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirming that the patch did not eliminate the out-of-bounds write.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The definition and size of the local `nesting` array in `mg_json_get`—how it [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrelates to the macros `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code paths in `mg_json_get` that increment or write into `nesting`, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparticularly around lines [0m[1;36m130[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m190[0m[39m of `src/json.c`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The parsing logic that drives the `depth`, `ci`, `ei`, and `pos` variables, to [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:            for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mei = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m; pos++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Unify and reconcile the “depth” and “nesting” macros so that the size of the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocal `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` buffer and the checks against excessive nesting use the *same* [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstant.  In practice:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Make MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING the single source-of-truth for the maximum allowed [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting level [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefaulting to [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Alias MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH to MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING for backward compatibility [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremove MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH if it is no longer used elsewhere[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. json.h changes:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove any standalone “#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH … #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m” block.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensure there is exactly one block for MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Immediately after, add:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH  MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     so that both macros are always equal.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Resulting snippet in `src/json.h`:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #pragma once[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #include [0m[32m"arch.h"[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #include [0m[32m"str.h"[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Alias for legacy code[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH  MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Error codes…[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. json.c changes:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Change the local buffer declaration from[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      to[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In the JSON‐object and JSON‐array open branches, replace *all* checks of the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mform[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      with[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e. use the same macro you used in the buffer declaration[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Optionally, for clarity, use the equivalent[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m …[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      since you want to reject any attempt to write past index [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING-[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Verify no other parts of `json.c` refer to the old MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH in a way [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat might reintroduce a mismatch.  Update those to use MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malias[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m uniformly.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Rebuild and rerun the AddressSanitizer fuzz target.  The buffer `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` will[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnow have exactly N slots, and every push into `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` will first check [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat `depth < N`, thereby eliminating the [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte stack overflow at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By unifying the buffer size and the overflow guard under the same macro [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we eliminate any possibility that the code allows deeper [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting than the buffer can hold.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changing the declaration [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m preserves the original [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwe still push/pop exactly one character per nest level[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Using the check `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguarantees we never write beyond the last valid slot [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`index [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING-[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- We avoid any changes to the fuzz harness or external test code, ensuring existing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests continue to pass.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This approach is used in similar codebases where the same macro governs both the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray size and the depth limit, preventing off-by-one [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors.<code_range>src/json.h:[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m16[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>src/json.[0m[1;92mc:126[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m134[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>src/json.[0m[1;92mc:165[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/22/25 01:50:38][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=16980;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=842943;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
