[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue involves a libFuzzer run triggering an AddressSanitizer [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow in the function `mg_json_get` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjson.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The local array [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting`, declared with size `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, is written out of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds when the JSON nesting depth exceeds that limit.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch attempt changed the macro definitions in `json.h`—swapping the order of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` so that `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefaults to [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m and `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` aliases it—and updated `json.c` to declare [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting` using `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` and to tighten the depth check from `>` to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`>=`.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch and rerunning the fuzzer, the same stack-buffer-overflow [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis reported at the same location, indicating the overflow persists.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A fuzzing harness invokes `mg_json_get` with crafted input, and AddressSanitizer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreports a one-byte write beyond the end of the local array `nesting`.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash trace shows `nesting` occupies stack offsets [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m62[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but code[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths in `mg_json_get` write at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, overflowing the array’s right redzone.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The buffer size macro `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` is set to [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m by default.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The call stack reaches `mg_json_get` with `depth` values that exceed the buffer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The error location is json.c line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m, within logic that tracks nesting levels.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/json.h`, the patch reverses the macro definitions:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #endif[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #endif[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/json.c`, the declaration and checks change from:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[33m...[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  to:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[33m...[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch is intended to enlarge the `nesting` buffer from [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m elements and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menforce the new limit strictly.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPost-Patch Log  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After recompiling with the patched headers and sources, the fuzzer still crashes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith an AddressSanitizer stack-buffer-overflow at the same location [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`json.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The reported stack frame and shadow bytes confirm `nesting` remains only [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwide in the generated object, and a write still lands at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, overflowing the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Verify that the build system picks up the updated macro definitions in `json.h` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand that `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` truly expands to [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m at compile time.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inspect the declaration of `nesting` in `mg_json_get` to confirm which macro it [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muses under all compilation configurations.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Examine the logic in `mg_json_get` that increments and indexes the `nesting` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray, ensuring all accesses respect the intended maximum depth.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Review any conditional compilation or include order in the JSON module that might[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverride or bypass the patched macro values.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Audit related JSON parsing routines for symmetry between declared buffer sizes [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand runtime checks on nesting/stack indices.[0m                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:165[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m174[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m165[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m j = i;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m166[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m167[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m168[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m && ci == ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m169[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m If we start the object, reset array indices[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m171[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m173[0m[39m:          expecting = S_KEY;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m174[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:175[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m && ei == ci[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:            for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mei = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m; pos++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:              ei *= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:167[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m168[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m167[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m168[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m && ci == ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:176[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m177[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m && ei == ci[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Align Buffer Size and Depth Checks  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `src/json.h`, consolidate and clarify the two macros so that [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` is always the authoritative capacity. Remove the old default [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and alias it explicitly to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`. For [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexample:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In `src/json.c`, change the local nesting buffer to use `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstead of `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m before[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m after[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Tighten Off-by-One Checks on Nesting Depth  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The existing code checks `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before writing into [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, which allows a write when `depth == MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`. [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mChange both brace- and bracket-handling branches from:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   to:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This prevents any write at index `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, keeping all accesses [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m .. MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING-[0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional [0m[35m/[0m[39m Safety[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Pre-increment Bound Check  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   For maximal clarity and to tie the check directly to the upcoming write, you can[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrewrite the two branches as:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m for [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m and similarly for [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This makes the capacity requirement [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`depth + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m <= max`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m explicit just before [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe write.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Verify Build-Time Macro Values  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   To ensure the patched header is actually picked up by all translation units:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add a compile-time sanity check at the top of `json.c`:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #if MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING < [0m[1;36m1[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #error [0m[32m"MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING must be defined and ≥ 1"[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #endif[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Perform a clean rebuild [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`make clean; make`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to remove any stale object files [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat might have been compiled with the old default of [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Regression Verification  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run the existing unit tests and fuzz harness to confirm no breakage and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mverify the AddressSanitizer no longer reports a stack-buffer-overflow in [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Monitor stack usage: increasing the buffer from [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m bytes is negligible, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut confirm that deeply nested JSON inputs beyond [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m levels still yield [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` rather than undefined behavior.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This approach directly addresses the root causes: the array was too small [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and the runtime checks were off by one, allowing writes at the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexact capacity.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It preserves all existing parsing logic and API surface: we only tweak macro [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefinitions and tighten guards.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer harness and test code remain untouched, ensuring existing tests still [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpass and that the same fuzzing entry points are used.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The compile-time check guards against future misconfiguration of the header.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Similar patterns are used elsewhere [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., other parsers that cap depth via `>= [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmax`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so this solution follows the project’s established style.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPotential Side-Effects & Mitigation  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Increased stack usage in `mg_json_get` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m~[0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes more[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This is minimal; if [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnecessary, one could allocate `nesting` dynamically, but for typical use cases [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes is acceptable.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If consumers of `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` expected it to be [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, this change makes it [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m; however, the alias ensures both macros match. Document the new default in the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchangelog.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stricter `>=` check disallows a final “slot” that previously could be [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpartially used; this is intended to prevent overflow and will simply cause [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` sooner.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A clean build is critical to ensure no old object files remain with the outdated [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmacro values.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe project’s JSON parsing function, `mg_json_get`, triggers a one-byte [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstack-buffer-overflow when run under AddressSanitizer during fuzz testing. The [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow occurs in a local `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[33m...[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` array. A patch was applied [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Swapped and renamed the `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` macros in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`json.h`.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added a compile-time `_Static_assert` for `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changed the array declaration in `json.c` to use `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adjusted the depth checks to use `>= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` instead of `> [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter rebuilding and re-running the fuzzer, the same stack-buffer-overflow is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreported at the same location in `mg_json_get`.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer runs `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` on the code in `mongoose/src/json.c`.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a stack-buffer-overflow in function `mg_json_get` at [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m of `json.c`.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow is a single-byte write just past the end of a local array named [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting`, which was originally declared with size `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack frame shows the `nesting` object spans addresses `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite happens at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, immediately beyond this array.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No other errors or crashes are shown in the log.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. In `src/json.h`:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Renamed `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mredefined `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` to alias `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensured the two macros cannot be misordered and added a guard [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35m_Static_assert[0m[1;39m([0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING >= [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In `src/json.c`:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Changed the local buffer declaration from `unsigned char [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` to `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Updated depth checks to `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;` for both `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` cases.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Rebuilt and re-ran the fuzzer with the same testcase.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLog After Patch  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer runs [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m iterations on the testcase without timing out.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer again reports a stack-buffer-overflow in `mg_json_get` at the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame line [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`json.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow still occurs at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m of the `nesting` buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow sized [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the buffer is still too small for the input path being processed.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No change in crash address or stack-frame layout is observed.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The implementation of `mg_json_get` around how `depth` and `ed` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexpected depth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
